    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2226241841" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2226241841" />
    <a title="Hanieh Habibi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2870591-hanieh-habibi"><img alt="Hanieh Habibi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1586431517p2/2870591.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2226241841?book_show_action=true">Feb 24, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hanieh Habibi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hanieh Habibi" href="/user/show/2870591-hanieh-habibi">Hanieh Habibi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook " href="/book/show/32070903">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2226241841" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12495932299378000361">It was not that much fascinating for me cause I already knew lots of things he mentioned. And also, if atheists follow all details in the religion, of course with other reasons, what is the difference between them and theists? I mean maybe the attitude of not caring about these issues makes them what they are!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

